    <list id="import-auto-id1166561866504" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic"><item>Q.5.Determine the Fermi Velocity of conduction electron in Metal Copper and Thermal Velocity of conduction electron or hole in Semi-conductor.</item>
    </list><para id="import-auto-id1166548409315">[Hint: </para>
    <para id="import-auto-id1166561841146"><figure id="import-auto-id1166535597346"><media id="import-auto-id1166546885644" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics3-bd7e.png" height="30" width="493"/></media></figure>]</para>
    <para id="import-auto-id1166546864837">{Answer : Fermi Velocity in Metal Copper is 2.7256×10<sup>6</sup>m/s and in semi-conductor Thermal Velocity is 1.17×10<sup>5</sup>m/s]</para>
    <list id="import-auto-id1166536035870" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic"><item>Q.6.In Copper, ρ(resisitivity)=1.67×10<sup>-8</sup>Ω-m and σ(conductivity)= 6×10<sup>7</sup>S/m = qμn. Where n=8.5×10<sup>28</sup>electrons/m<sup>3</sup>. Determine conduction electron mobility. [ 40cm<sup>2</sup>/(V-s)]</item>
      <item> Q.7. 3 m long Copper wire of R= 0.03Ω and the current I through the wire is 15A.</item>
    </list><list id="import-auto-id1166531115732" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha">
      <item>Determine Voltage Drop across the Wire.[0.45V]</item>
      <item>Determine the Electric Field within the Wire.[0.15V/m]</item>
      <item>Determine the drift velocity of electron within the wire.[0.6×10<sup>-3</sup>m/s]</item>
      <item>Determine the Fermi Velocity.[2.7256×10<sup>6</sup>m/s]</item>
      <item>Determine the Mean Free Time or Relaxation Time.[2.27×10<sup>-14</sup>s]</item>
      <item>Determine the Mean Free Path and compare with the lattice parameter of Copper.[618A°]</item>
    </list>
    <list id="import-auto-id1166541096571" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic"><item>Q.8. Typical Resistivity of N-Type Silicon is 1 Ω-cm and typical current density is 100A/cm<sup>2</sup>. Calculate the applied Electric Field in Silicon Sample and calculate the drift velocity. Assume mobility of electron to be 1400cm<sup>2</sup>/(V-s) [Answer:100V/cm and 140×10<sup>3</sup>cm/s]</item>
      <item> Q.9. Calculate the intrinsic resistivity of Ge, Si and GaAs. [107Ω-cm; 3.4×10<sup>5</sup>Ω-cm; 7×10<sup>8</sup>Ω-cm].</item>
      <item>Q.10. In all the calculations above we have assumed that the effective mass of electron or hole within the solid is the same whereas it is not true. The effective mass in Metals are generally higher than the free space mass and in semiconductors it is lighter as seen from the Table below.</item>
